# Use @sbox Docs for s&box API Questions

When something in s&box is not behaving as expected — unexpected API results, physics not responding, component methods missing, or uncertain about the correct API — **stop and check the indexed docs (or s&box MCP) before guessing**.

Do **not** guess at s&box APIs from general C#/Unity/Godot knowledge. s&box has its own component model and physics API.

## Indexed Cursor docs (use the right @ mention)

| When working on… | @ mention |
|------------------|-----------|
| General / unsure where to look | `@Dev Docs Hub` |
| Method signatures, component APIs, types | `@API Reference` |
| `[Sync]`, RPCs, ownership, visibility, dedicated servers | `@Networking` |
| 2-window MP, `connect local`, editor join testing | `@MP Testing` |
| Weapons, inventory, hold poses, `BaseCombatWeapon` (slice 7+) | `@Inventory and Weapons` |
| Physics hub — rigidbodies, colliders, triggers overview | `@Physics` |
| `Scene.Trace`, ray/sphere/box sweeps, collision rules, LOS | `@Physics Tracing` |
| Panels, `PanelComponent`, ScreenPanel vs WorldPanel | `@UI` |
| Razor HUDs, `BuildHash`, `.razor` / `.razor.scss` | `@UI Razor` |
| **Our** host authority, client predict, combat feel dedupe | `MULTIPLAYER_NETCODE.md` (repo — not s&box) |

## Rule

- Use the **most specific** indexed doc from the table above — do **not** ask Max to `@` generic docs if a row already matches the task.
- If you already tried an API and it didn't work, reach for the indexed doc (or MCP console) before a second guess.
- Engine **news/changelogs** are not indexed — Max pastes the update link when a fresh engine change matters. Do not rely on stale news crawls.
- Optional sitemap: https://sbox.game/llms.txt

## s&box editor MCP (when editor is open)

- Cursor MCP `sbox` → `http://127.0.0.1:7269/mcp` (editor must be open with Ultimate Throwdown loaded).
- **OK without asking:** `editor_status`, `read_console`, read-only inspection, screenshots, asset/scene queries.
- **Still needs Max's explicit yes in that chat:** any MCP tool that edits scenes, prefabs, materials, or other editor-owned assets (same as `editor-asset-ownership.mdc`).

## Common areas that need docs (not Unity muscle memory)

- `Scene.Trace` / ray-sphere-box sweeps, collision rules, triggers
- `ModelPhysics` / ragdoll body velocity and impulse
- `PhysicsGroup` / `PhysicsBody` methods
- `NetworkSpawn` / `[Sync]` / `[Rpc.Host]` patterns
- `PlayerController` internals (capsule, collision, grounding)
- Razor `PanelComponent`, `WorldPanel`, `ScreenPanel`, `.razor.scss`
- Any unfamiliar component property or method
